page.title: 03WILDLIFE ALONG THE SEAWALL
page.content: As one walks along the seawall one can see a lot of wildlife. Halfway down the seawall we found lots of dead crabs,most of then were shore crabs. There were quite afew sandhoppers under big rocks in the mud.Along the seawall consisted of daisies,thistles,barley and grasses. Out in the mud there is yellow_green saltmarsh,on top of the seawall and down at the opposite side from the mud there were again lots of different grasses and plants. Also there is a lot of birds you can see like{Geese,Herring Gulls, {Common Gulls,Ducks}and if one is very lucky the odd{Cormorant or Shag.
